<dl id="n12012c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12012c">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12012c"> 12(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> chastening his style</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">A toute &eacute;poque, il y a eu &eacute;videmment une l&eacute;g&egrave;re diff&eacute;rence entre le style familier et le ch&acirc;ti&eacute;; mais ils ne s&apos;opposent point comme font deux langues &eacute;trang&egrave;res dans le Moi d&apos;un polyglotte. <br><font color="green">[In every age there is always a slight difference between the familiar style and <mark>the chastened style</mark>; but they do not differ as two foreign languages do within the Ego of a polyglot.]</font> <small> Jacques Boulenger &amp; Andr&eacute; Th&eacute;rive, <a name="SOIR" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#SOIR"><cite title="source">Les Soir&eacute;es du Grammaire-Club</cite></a> (1924) 158</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
